supported modes:
  - 1332x990 @ 120fps
  - 2028x1080 @ 50fps
  - 2028x1520 @ 40fps
  - 4056x3040 @ 10fps

SOLUTION:
---------
1. Auto-detect camera capabilities from libcamera-hello
2. Select best matching mode from available resolutions
3. Use videoscale to resize if needed
4. Fallback to safe default (2028x1520 @ 40fps)

KEY IMPROVEMENTS:
----------------
✅ Parses libcamera-hello output to find available modes
✅ Selects best mode using scoring system
✅ Adds videoscale to pipeline when needed
✅ Cleaner code with mode detection
✅ Works with any libcamera-compatible camera

TESTING:
--------
1. Check detected modes in startup log
2. Verify selected resolution
3. Confirm frames are published

If still fails, run manually:
  libcamera-hello --list-cameras
  
And use one of the listed resolutions exactly.
